author: Scott Manley
description:
Hailed as a radical leap forward in technology by Russian media, while the rest of the world is a lot more skeptical, Russia's Burevestnik cruise missile made a successful test flight demonstrating its ability to fly in circles at near the speed of sound for 15 hours. Reanimating a concept the US abandoned in the 1960's as too provocative.
